<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB07898</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT PROHIBITING THE IMPOSITION OF INTEREST AND/OR PENALTY CHARGES ON UNPAID HOSPITAL BILLS AND MEDICAL EXPENSES OF PATIENTS WHO EARN MINIMUM WAGE OR LESS</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Penalizes any officer or employee of the hospital or medical clinic responsible for billing who violates the provision of this Act with a fine of not less than Twenty Thousand Pesos (Php20,000.00) but not more than Fifty Thousand Pesos (Php50,000.00), or imprisonment of not less than one (1) month but not more than six (6) months, or both such fine and imprisonment, at the discretion of the proper court.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>VILLARICA, LINABELLE RUTH R.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2018-07-02</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Del Mar (000 2018-08-07)</td><td>2. Vergara (000 2018-09-18)</td><tr><td>3. Chipeco (000 2018-10-10)</td><td>4. Suansing (E.) (000 2018-10-15)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON HEALTH ON 2018-07-30</td></tr></table>